    'Policy briefs should be written for readers who are knowledgeable but not academic specialists. Avoid jargon, define technical terms, and use active sentences. Recommendations should be specific enough that a reader can act on them: "the Ministry of Education should..." not "policymakers should consider...".': '政策简报应面向具有相关知识但并非学术专家的读者撰写。避免行话，定义技术术语，并使用主动句。建议应具体到读者可以据此行动，例如写作“教育部应……”，而不是“政策制定者应考虑……”。',
    'Research Report Template': '研究报告模板',
