    'Request Permission': '申請許可',
    'Governance Policy': '治理政策',
    'The official template for preparing policy briefs for Panorama Research Institute\'s policy brief series. Designed for concise, evidence-based, and audience-focused policy communication.': '用於撰寫全景研究院政策簡報系列的官方範本，面向簡明、循證且以讀者為中心的政策傳播。',
    'Template Details': '範本資訊',
    'Microsoft Word (.docx)': 'Microsoft Word（.docx）',
    'v1.0 (2026)': 'v1.0（2026）',
    'Policymakers, institutional leaders, practitioners': '政策制定者、機構領導者、實踐者',
    'Download Template': '下載範本',
    'Policy Brief Structure': '政策簡報結構',
    'Policy briefs follow a structured format designed to communicate effectively with policy audiences. Unlike academic papers, policy briefs lead with conclusions and emphasize practical recommendations. The template enforces this structure and includes style guidance for each section.': '政策簡報採用結構化格式，旨在面向政策讀者進行有效傳播。不同於學術論文，政策簡報以結論開篇，並強調實踐性建議。範本強化這一結構，並為各部分提供風格指南。',
    'Title, brief number, author(s), research center, date, DOI': '標題、簡報編號、作者、研究中心、日期、DOI',
    'Key Messages': '關鍵資訊',
    '3–5 bullet points; the brief\'s essential conclusions; appears before the text body': '3–5 條要點；簡報核心結論；位於正文之前',
    '150–250 words; for readers who will read no further': '150–250 詞；面向只閱讀摘要的讀者',
    'The policy problem or question the brief addresses; why it matters now': '簡報回應的政策問題或議題；說明其當下重要性',
    'The evidence base; structured analysis; clearly distinguished from opinion': '證據基礎；結構化分析；明確區別於觀點',
    'Realistic options for action; advantages and limitations of each': '現實可行的行動選項；各選項優點與限制',
    'Specific, actionable recommendations; addressed to a named audience': '具體、可操作的建議；面向明確對象',
    'Essential references only; inline or endnote style; not a full bibliography': '僅列必要參考文獻；可用文內或尾註格式；不是完整書目',
    'Standard Institute description (pre-filled, do not alter)': '研究院標準說明（已預填，請勿修改）',
    'Writing Guidance': '寫作指南',
    'Policy briefs should be written for readers who are knowledgeable but not academic specialists. Avoid jargon, define technical terms, and use active sentences. Recommendations should be specific enough that a reader can act on them: "the Ministry of Education should..." not "policymakers should consider...".': '政策簡報應面向具有相關知識但並非學術專家的讀者撰寫。避免行話，定義技術術語，並使用主動句。建議應具體到讀者可以據此行動，例如寫作「教育部應……」，而不是「政策制定者應考慮……」。',
    'Research Report Template': '研究報告範本',
    'The official template for preparing research reports for Panorama Research Institute\'s report series. Includes full structure, formatting specifications, and section guidance.': '用於撰寫全景研究院報告系列研究報告的官方範本，包含完整結構、格式規範和章節指南。',
    'Report Structure': '報告結構',
    'Research reports must follow the Institute\'s standard structure. The template provides pre-formatted sections, style definitions, and placeholder content for all required elements. Authors should not alter the section order or remove required elements.': '研究報告必須遵循研究院標準結構。範本為所有必需元素提供預設章節、樣式定義和佔位內容。作者不應調整章節順序或刪除必需元素。',
    'Title, report number, author(s), date, research center, DOI': '標題、報告編號、作者、日期、研究中心、DOI',
    'Standard Institute disclaimer (pre-filled, do not alter)': '研究院標準免責聲明（已預填，請勿修改）',
    '200–300 words; no citations in abstract': '200–300 詞；摘要中不引用文獻',
    '5–8 keywords, comma-separated': '5–8 個關鍵詞，以逗號分隔',
    'List of Tables / Figures': '表格 / 圖示清單',
    'Required if >3 tables or figures': '如超過 3 個表格或圖示則必需',
    '800–1,200 words; self-contained summary for non-specialist readers': '800–1,200 詞；面向非專業讀者的獨立摘要',
    'Context, rationale, research questions, report structure': '背景、理由、研究問題、報告結構',
